⭐ 3. DATA DEPENDENCY MAP (Global Variables)

	This shows which routine reads/writes which global variable.

	Code

	VARIABLE       READ BY     WRITTEN BY
	------------------------------------------------
	d063A2         s8          external init
	d06035 (X1)    s8, s9      s8
	d06037 (Y1)    s8, s9      s8
	d06039 (X2)    s8, s9      s8
	d0603B (Y2)    s8, s9      s8

	d06020–d0602E  s9          s9 (initialization)
	d06024         s9          s9 (initialization)

	d06010[]       s7          external init

	Framebuffer    s7          s7

	Key Insight:

	s8 is the only writer of coordinate registers.

	s9 is the only writer of Bresenham state.

	s7 is the only writer of framebuffer bytes.

⭐ 4. EXECUTION DEPENDENCY MAP (Control‑Flow)

	This shows conditional dependencies — which paths depend on which conditions.

	Code

	d063A2 == 0x02 → s8 returns immediately
	d063A2 == 0x00 → s8 calls b067e1()
	else           → s8 performs 4-pass rendering

	Each pass → s9()

	Inside s9:
	  dx, dy depend on coordinate registers
	  step increments depend on dx/dy
	  loop count depends on d06024
	  each iteration depends on bx sign

	Inside s7:
	  mask depends on (si & 3)
	  offset depends on calculate_offset()
	  pixel value depends on AH

	This is the true dependency logic of the subsystem.

